01:01:34.869 --> 01:01:38.130
Developing countries can do handmade things.

01:01:38.130 --> 01:01:41.869
You cannot beat them with computers.

01:01:41.869 --> 01:01:43.849
Can you?

01:01:43.849 --> 01:01:47.200
You go ahead, mad with your computers.

01:01:47.200 --> 01:01:49.410
You'll have to come back.

01:01:49.410 --> 01:01:52.599
You must understand the whole.

01:01:52.599 --> 01:01:56.730
If you don't understand the whole, this is
what is happening: like mad, you know computers

01:01:56.730 --> 01:01:58.580
are going ahead, ahead.

01:01:58.580 --> 01:01:59.580
Where?

01:01:59.580 --> 01:02:02.880
Into the ditch, into a big mountain.

01:02:02.880 --> 01:02:12.050
Now they have created a big mountains of plastic
and they don't know what to do with it.

01:02:12.050 --> 01:02:17.780
So, and now with computer, what will they
do?

01:02:17.780 --> 01:02:22.190
They'll create a greater mountains out of
plastics.

01:02:22.190 --> 01:02:26.670
Maybe a Himalaya might be created, with the
computer.

01:02:26.670 --> 01:02:32.630
So the developing countries should not try
to follow these mad people on one side.

01:02:32.630 --> 01:02:36.730
They should develop their hand things and
all that, because they'll have to come back.

01:02:36.730 --> 01:02:42.060
Now, the handmade things in this country are
so important and so expensive.

01:02:42.060 --> 01:02:45.470
You don't care whether it is pressed or not.

01:02:45.470 --> 01:02:54.340
But in India you have to take nylons, because
they say nylons is a symbol of development,

01:02:54.340 --> 01:02:57.400
not of over-development, perhaps, but of development.

01:02:57.400 --> 01:03:03.160
So they must take to nylons and plastics and
to stainless steel and aluminium, if possible.

01:03:03.160 --> 01:03:04.320
That's what we are doing.

01:03:04.320 --> 01:03:11.740
When you have less things consumed like that,
you use less things from your motherland,

01:03:11.740 --> 01:03:16.610
because handmade you cannot go on mad like
a machine goes, like a rakshasa eating away

01:03:16.610 --> 01:03:17.610
everything and producing more.

01:03:17.610 --> 01:03:19.200
She has to live like that.

01:03:19.200 --> 01:03:22.590
It's not economical.

01:03:22.590 --> 01:03:26.070
So when you have handmade things you have
more value for your things, you look after

01:03:26.070 --> 01:03:35.990
them better, you feel better, you are comfortable
and you need not be that smart, you see, machine-made.

01:03:35.990 --> 01:03:38.180
That idea of smartness is going down.

01:03:38.180 --> 01:03:41.730
So, the developing countries should also learn
a lesson.

01:03:41.730 --> 01:03:42.820
They are going after you.

01:03:42.820 --> 01:03:43.820
They are running fast.

01:03:43.820 --> 01:03:45.840
They try to run faster; they cannot.

01:03:45.840 --> 01:03:49.050
Thank God, they cannot.

01:03:49.050 --> 01:03:50.720
But they should stick on to that side.

01:03:50.720 --> 01:03:54.540
You see, one part of the country has to do
something; another part has to do something

01:03:54.540 --> 01:03:55.540
else.

01:03:55.540 --> 01:04:02.780
But, you people have to look after the side
of machines, all right?

01:04:02.780 --> 01:04:07.530
I mean, handmade things, what can you make?

01:04:07.530 --> 01:04:15.619
Some ceramics, I think - apologies, some apologies
for that.

01:04:15.619 --> 01:04:19.990
You better do what you know better and let
them do what they can do better and share

01:04:19.990 --> 01:04:20.990
it.

01:04:20.990 --> 01:04:32.800
If this balance is established, there's no
aggression.

01:04:32.800 --> 01:04:34.130
Unemployment can be solved.

01:04:34.130 --> 01:04:36.770
All the problems can be solved, if you take
to handmade things.

01:04:36.770 --> 01:04:40.060
You should take to handmade things as far
as possible.

01:04:40.060 --> 01:04:42.990
Sahaja yogis should use handmade things.

01:04:42.990 --> 01:04:48.670
I mean, not the cars, but for their personal
use.

01:04:48.670 --> 01:04:54.040
Even I would say, soaps that you use are horrid.

01:04:54.040 --> 01:04:59.510
The soaps that you get in England are not
meant for your skins at all, for sahaja yogis'

01:04:59.510 --> 01:05:00.510
skin.

01:05:00.510 --> 01:05:01.630
I can't bear them.

01:05:01.630 --> 01:05:09.830
What you have to use is natural soaps that
you get from any country you feel like, but

01:05:09.830 --> 01:05:12.990
natural soaps, which come from natural oils.

01:05:12.990 --> 01:05:20.620
Foods also, natural food you must eat, more
natural food, than artificial.

01:05:20.620 --> 01:05:25.710
All that will give you a better living and
that is called as alternative, all right.

01:05:25.710 --> 01:05:30.960
That's alternative is important, but that
doesn't mean you go on a bullock cart.

01:05:30.960 --> 01:05:37.080
You can export your trains to India, or your
cars to India and get khadi from there.

01:05:37.080 --> 01:05:38.940
All right?

01:05:38.940 --> 01:05:46.520
Mutual understanding, because we are part
and parcel of one whole and we just cannot

01:05:46.520 --> 01:05:50.700
exist by our only growth because then we become
malignant, you see.

01:05:50.700 --> 01:05:51.700
One cells eats another.

01:05:51.700 --> 01:05:52.700
You have to.

01:05:52.700 --> 01:05:58.400
If you have a machinery, you have to eat other,
because you produce so much.

01:05:58.400 --> 01:06:02.080
You must find markets for them, you must supply
them, you must send over and then you must

01:06:02.080 --> 01:06:06.560
have other countries to exploit them.

01:06:06.560 --> 01:06:10.200
People have tremendous respect for Mahatma
Gandhi, but I don't know if people understand

01:06:10.200 --> 01:06:13.370
what he said about machinery.

01:06:13.370 --> 01:06:17.410
That doesn't mean the people who are doing
machine work should give up, by any chance,

01:06:17.410 --> 01:06:20.910
but, some of them they can close down.

01:06:20.910 --> 01:06:27.650
For example, plastic toys for children is
horrifying.

01:06:27.650 --> 01:06:32.280
You can't even get wood toys now - nothing,
just plastic.

01:06:32.280 --> 01:06:33.280
They are touching plastic.

01:06:33.280 --> 01:06:36.480
I mean, imagine, you cannot feel any plastic.

01:06:36.480 --> 01:06:44.990
So, this is what a sane sahaja yogi has to
understand.

01:06:44.990 --> 01:06:48.450
That's how you can solve the problem of environment,
also.

01:06:48.450 --> 01:07:01.730
Thank God, somehow with your affluence and
too much of machinery, all the western people

01:07:01.730 --> 01:07:08.280
- I am happy to know, even in Portugal - realize
the value of handmade things.

01:07:08.280 --> 01:07:15.339
But in India if you offer somebody in an handmade
thing they'll say, "Oh God, they have no money."

01:07:15.339 --> 01:07:23.070
But stainless steel, "Great."

01:07:23.070 --> 01:07:26.870
In a stainless steel, glass they'll give you
tea, you see - it's very big.

01:07:26.870 --> 01:07:33.260
If you give it in a ceramic, "Oh, what this,
village craft?"

01:07:33.260 --> 01:07:36.520
They are to be told.

01:07:36.520 --> 01:07:40.900
But, if you create a demand, they'll be all
right; they'll look after their handmade.

01:07:40.900 --> 01:07:43.140
And here you can't do much.

01:07:43.140 --> 01:07:47.980
I've seen, you see, that neatness, that deftness
is not there; that's lacking; now they've

01:07:47.980 --> 01:07:48.980
lost it.

01:07:48.980 --> 01:07:50.770
Very few people have that left in them.

01:07:50.770 --> 01:07:55.370
Even if they have to cut one coat with their
hands, they cannot do it.

01:07:55.370 --> 01:08:02.890
They have to use a machine, which cuts twenty-five
coats at a time, you see.

01:08:02.890 --> 01:08:09.200
Then this problem of, you have to have a figure
exactly because these only can fit certain

01:08:09.200 --> 01:08:10.200
figures.

01:08:10.200 --> 01:08:11.410
You can't have your own independent figure.

01:08:11.410 --> 01:08:13.690
This is all machine-like stuff, you see.

01:08:13.690 --> 01:08:16.150
You all must have that figure, otherwise doesn't
fit it.

01:08:16.150 --> 01:08:17.779
So, that is an ideal figure.

01:08:17.779 --> 01:08:19.540
So, everybody works out for that.

01:08:19.540 --> 01:08:23.880
See, there's a new machinery comes up, you
see, for that kind of a thing, then new styles

01:08:23.880 --> 01:08:26.799
come up.

01:08:26.799 --> 01:08:30.910
It's such an artificial thing, all man-made,
artificial.

01:08:30.910 --> 01:08:41.959
From your democracy, your politics to your
economics, to all your so-called ideas of

01:08:41.959 --> 01:08:45.299
creativity, everything becomes so artificial.

01:08:45.299 --> 01:08:46.909
Now people can't paint.

01:08:46.909 --> 01:08:51.499
What they paint, if you see, you are just
aghast.

01:08:51.499 --> 01:08:54.909
You don't know what is this supposed to be.

01:08:54.909 --> 01:08:57.069
And it is supposed to be so that it looks,
"There's a hand, isn't it?

01:08:57.069 --> 01:08:58.949
Can't you see that?"

01:08:58.949 --> 01:09:01.509
"Yes, I can.

01:09:01.509 --> 01:09:05.769
It's a little bit showing."

01:09:05.769 --> 01:09:07.369
They can't do anything.

01:09:07.369 --> 01:09:19.660
We can't have Shakespeare, we can't have Gauguin,
we can't have anyone of that type.

01:09:19.660 --> 01:09:25.460
We can't have, say, Abraham Lincoln.

01:09:25.460 --> 01:09:32.019
You can have only machines, you see, bolts
and nuts, fitted nicely.

01:09:32.019 --> 01:09:35.209
You're fixed, you're fixed, you're fixed,
you're fixed.

01:09:35.209 --> 01:09:36.209
Everybody fixed nicely.

01:09:36.209 --> 01:09:39.309
Where do, I mean, this brain go?

01:09:39.309 --> 01:09:40.459
Where will this heart go?

01:09:40.459 --> 01:09:43.270
What will it do then?

01:09:43.270 --> 01:09:44.270
It cannot collapse.

01:09:44.270 --> 01:09:48.639
I mean, as long as you are existing, the heart
has to beat.

01:09:48.639 --> 01:09:55.559
01:09:53 So all this artificiality has to
be overcome by sahaja yogis.

01:09:55.559 --> 01:09:58.119
The responsibility is so great.

01:09:58.119 --> 01:10:08.070
Such a big building you have to bear on your
shoulders, and the foundation stones have

01:10:08.070 --> 01:10:16.369
to get up in the morning to be chiseled out
properly.

01:10:16.369 --> 01:10:20.260
So, I end up My lecture today.

01:10:20.260 --> 01:10:22.480
May God bless you!

01:10:22.480 --> 01:10:25.249
Now I am getting self-conscious.

01:10:25.249 --> 01:10:28.579
Will you please put it off?

01:10:28.579 --> 01:10:29.690
All right.

